        "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/1/13/5131",
        "text": [
          ": سُئِلَ أَحَدُهُمَا عَلَيْهِمَا اَلسَّلاَمُ عَنْ حَدِّ اَلْأَخْرَسِ وَ اَلْأَصَمِّ وَ اَلْأَعْمَى قَالَ \"عَلَيْهِمُ اَلْحُدُودُ إِذَا كَانُوا يَعْقِلُونَ مَا يَأْتُونَ\"."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
            "Hadith.5131 - Yunus narrated from Ishaq ibn Ammar who said that one of the two Imams (peace be upon them) was asked about the legal punishments (hudud) for a mute, a deaf person, and a blind person.\nImam (as) said: \"The legal punishments apply to them if they comprehend what they are doing.\""
          ]
        }
      }
